<br>
Anyway, just played some hours in splitpaw. We were camped at the barrel room. My pet was travelling the room better than I was. <br>
A mob at my feets trying to kill me and another on the pet. <br>
The one on the pet die and my pet just travel to the end of the room tries to come back to help me (nice litte pet) than got the aggro of a pop. <br>
/me Call Gegober &quot;Back off please I need you&quot;<br>
/pet Gegober says &quot;I am busy right now please call later. Hey come on you can solo this even without me&quot;. <br>
Finally after several &quot;spell interrupted&quot; The mob on me start to flee. Cool, I made it. Problem not enought mana to finish it. <br>
The mob use the same awfull pathing as the pet. The mob regen a bit but at the same time meet some friends and ask for support. Awsome, mobs have support of their friends, I can't even have the support of my pet. <br>
Now while medding I have 3 mobs &quot;tapping their foot impatiently&quot; and looking at me :-) /mob says You touched our friends little nasty Dark Elf Girl ? We'll take care of your virginity !!!<br>
<br>
/me thinking of the courageous technique &quot;FLEEeeee.....&quot;<br>
<br>
3 mobs using 2 different pathing call some pop for (who said this game was not based on communication networks) support at the same time and I finish with a nice train and a nice command result &quot;You don't have a pet to command&quot;.<br>
<br>
Near reaching the zone, &quot;You have been slained by an Hash something Gnole&quot; &quot;Loading please&quot;.<br>
<br>
Conclusions :<br>
- easy corps run I was near the zone.<br>
- So easy it was frustating.<br>
- better conclusion. Sometime pathing of the NPC/Mobs are also something you can use at your advantage. I am sure I am not the only one that discovered this (even if I am the latest one:-) ).<br>
- If Verant fix the pet pathing they will correct the mob pathing too. Should be like this too. But let's see the funny part Verrant fix the mob pathing and than patch the proggies in such a way that pet pathing is still an heavy @#%$.<br>
<br>
Anyway it is a short storry to say YEAH GREAT IDEA I want it. I hope that if Verrant didn't know what pathing problems are, they'll read this and will finally try to fix it.<br>
