nt machine indicating that he is in battle.  The client machine can then take care of computing whether or not the hotkey can be used. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucalebe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Calebe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#333333>(12/12/01 6:00:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=47.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   A possible easy fix for pet pathing</span><hr size=1> Wonderful idea, a /pet hotkey would be ideal.<br>
